st %1$s backups in %2$s'=>'store the last %1$s backups in %2$s','don\'t store any backups in on this server'=>'don\'t store any backups in on this server','store the most recent backup in %s'=>'store the most recent backup in %s','manually'=>'manually','on the %1$s of each month at %2$s'=>'on the %1$s of each month at %2$s','weekly on %1$s at %2$s'=>'weekly on %1$s at %2$s','every 12 hours at %1$s &amp; %2$s'=>'every 12 hours at %1$s &amp; %2$s','daily at %s'=>'daily at %s','hourly at %s minutes past the hour'=>'hourly at %s minutes past the hour','hourly on the hour'=>'hourly on the hour','The next backup will be on %1$s at %2$s %3$s'=>'The next backup will be on %1$s at %2$s %3$s','This schedule will store a maximum of %s of backups.'=>'This schedule will store a maximum of %s of backups.','Past this limit older backups will be deleted automatically.'=>'Past this limit older backups will be deleted automatically.','Number of backups to store on this server'=>'Number of backups to store on this server','The second backup will run 12 hours after the first.'=>'The second backup will run 12 hours after the first.','Minutes'=>'Minutes','Hours'=>'Hours','Start Time'=>'Start Time','Start Day of Month'=>'Start Day of Month','Sunday'=>'Sunday','Saturday'=>'Saturday','Friday'=>'Friday','Thursday'=>'Thursday','Wednesday'=>'Wednesday','Tuesday'=>'Tuesday','Monday'=>'Monday','Start Day'=>'Start Day','Manual Only'=>'Manual Only','Schedule'=>'Schedule','Database only'=>'Database only','Files only'=>'Files only','Both Database &amp; files'=>'Both Database &amp; files','Backup'=>'Backup','Settings'=>'Settings','Done'=>'Done','Exclude &rarr;'=>'Exclude &rarr;','Excluded'=>'Excluded','Unreadable'=>'Unreadable','Unreadable files won\'t be backed up.'=>'Unreadable files won\'t be backed up.','File'=>'File','Folder'=>'Folder','Symlink'=>'Symlink','Refresh'=>'Refresh','Status'=>'Status','Permissions'=>'Permissions','Name'=>'Name','Here\'s a directory listing of all files on your site, you can browse through and exclude files or folders that you don\'t want included in your backup.'=>'Here\'s a directory listing of all files on your site, you can browse through and exclude files or folders that you don\'t want included in your backup.','Stop excluding'=>'Stop excluding','Default rule'=>'Default rule','Currently Excluded'=>'Currently Excluded','If you\'re finding BackUpWordPress useful, please %1$s rate it on the plugin directory%2$s.'=>'If you\'re finding BackUpWordPress useful, please %1$s rate it on the plugin directory%2$s.','Help with translation'=>'Help with translation','Support Forums'=>'Support Forums','For more information:'=>'For more information:','Server Info'=>'Server Info','FAQ'=>'FAQ','Backups'=>'Backups','Manage Backups'=>'Manage Backups','My backups seem to be failing?'=>'My backups seem to be failing?','The script to be entered into the Heart Internet cPanel is: <code>/usr/bin/php5 /home/sites/yourdomain.com/public_html/wp-cron.php</code> (note the space between php5 and the location of the file). The file <code>wp-cron.php</code> <code>chmod</code> must be set to <code>711</code>.'=>'The script to be entered into the Heart Internet cPanel is: <code>/usr/bin/php5 /home/sites/yourdomain.com/public_html/wp-cron.php</code> (note the space between php5 and the location of the file). The file <code>wp-cron.php</code> <code>chmod</code> must be set to <code>711</code>.','How to get BackUpWordPress working in Heart Internet'=>'How to get BackUpWordPress working in Heart Internet','Is your site private (i.e. is it behind some kind of authentication, maintenance plugin, .htaccess)? If so, wp-cron won\'t work until you remove it. If you are and you temporarily remove the authentication, do backups start working?'=>'Is your site private (i.e. is it behind some kind of authentication, maintenance plugin, .htaccess)? If so, wp-cron won\'t work until you remove it. If you are and you temporarily remove the authentication, do backups start working?','Try adding <code>define( \'ALTERNATE_WP_CRON\', true );</code> to your <code>wp-config.php</code>. Do automatic backups work?'=>'Try adding <code>define( \'ALTERNATE_WP_CRON\', true );</code> to your <code>wp-config.php</code>. Do automatic backups work?','If you click manual backup, does it work?'=>'If you click manual backup, does it work?','Are you hosted on Heart Internet? (wp-cron may not be supported by Heart Internet, see below for work-around.)'=>'Are you hosted on Heart Internet? (wp-cron may not be supported by Heart Internet, see below for work-around.)','Are scheduled posts working? (They use wp-cron as well.)'=>'Are scheduled posts working? (They use wp-cron as well.)','There are some things you can test to confirm this is the issue.'=>'There are some things you can test to confirm this is the issue.','The issue is that your <code>wp-cron.php</code> is not returning a <code>200</code> response when hit with a HTTP request originating from your own server, it could be several things. In most cases, it\'s an issue with the server / site.'=>'The issue is that your <code>wp-cron.php</code> is not returning a <code>200</code> response when hit with a HTTP request originating from your own server, it could be several things. In most cases, it\'s an issue with the server / site.','What do I do if I get the wp-cron error message?'=>'What do I do if I get the wp-cron error message?','Unless your site is very large (many gigabytes) it should only take a few minutes to perform a backup. If your back up has been running for longer than an hour, it\'s safe to assume that something has gone wrong. Try de-activating and re-activating the plugin. If it keeps happening, contact support.'=>'Unless your site is very large (many gigabytes) it should only take a few minutes to perform a backup. If your back up has been running for longer than an hour, it\'s safe to assume that something has gone wrong. Try de-activating and re-activating the plugin. If it keeps happening, contact support.','How long should a backup take?'=>'How long should a backup take?','BackUpWordPress stores the last 10 backups by default.'=>'BackUpWordPress stores the last 10 backups by default.','How many backups are stored by default?'=>'How many backups are stored by default?','Most servers have a filesize limit on email attachments, it\'s generally about 10mb. If your backup file is over that limit, it won\'t be sent attached to the email. Instead, you should receive an email with a link to download the backup. If you aren\'t even receiving that, then you likely have a mail issue on your server that you\'ll need to contact your host about.'=>'Most servers have a filesize limit on email attachments, it\'s generally about 10mb. If your backup file is over that limit, it won\'t be sent attached to the email. Instead, you should receive an email with a link to download the backup. If you aren\'t even receiving that, then you likely have a mail issue on your server that you\'ll need to contact your host about.','I\'m not receiving my backups by email'=>'I\'m not receiving my backups by email','No.'=>'No.','Does BackUpWordPress back up the backups directory?'=>'Does BackUpWordPress back up the backups directory?','See this guide for more details - <a href="https://bwp.hmn.md/support-center/restore-backup/" title="Go to support center" target="_blank">How to restore from backup</a>.'=>'See this guide for more details - <a href="https://bwp.hmn.md/support-center/restore-backup/" title="Go to support center" target="_blank">How to restore from backup</a>.','You need to download the latest backup file either by clicking download on the backups page or via <code>FTP</code>. <code>Unzip</code> the files and upload all the files to your server overwriting your site. You can then import the database using your hosts database management tool (likely <code>phpMyAdmin</code>).'=>'You need to download the latest backup file either by clicking download on the backups page or via <code>FTP</code>. <code>Unzip</code> the files and upload all the files to your server overwriting your site. You can then import the database using your hosts database management tool (likely <code>phpMyAdmin</code>).','How do I restore my site from a backup?'=>'How do I restore my site from a backup?','What if I want to back up my site to another destination?'=>'What if I want to back up my site to another destination?','Important: By default BackUpWordPress backs up everything in your site root as well as your database, this includes any non WordPress folders that happen to be in your site root. This does mean that your backup directory can get quite large.'=>'Important: By default BackUpWordPress backs up everything in your site root as well as your database, this includes any non WordPress folders that happen to be in your site root. This does mean that your backup directory can get quite large.','Backups are stored on your server in <code>/wp-content/backups</code>, you can change the directory.'=>'Backups are stored on your server in <code>/wp-content/backups</code>, you can change the directory.','Where does BackUpWordPress store the backup files?'=>'Where does BackUpWordPress store the backup files?','Yes, I want to enable support'=>'Yes, I want to enable support','No, thanks'=>'No, thanks','You can disable support in the future by deactivating BackUpWordPress.'=>'You can disable support in the future by deactivating BackUpWordPress.','BackUpWordPress uses %s to provide support. In addition to allowing you to send and receive messages we also send the following server information along with your requests:'=>'BackUpWordPress uses %s to provide support. In addition to allowing you to send and receive messages we also send the following server information along with your requests:','Enable BackUpWordPress Support'=>'Enable BackUpWordPress Support','The time that your schedules should run. Defaults to %s.'=>'The time that your schedules should run. Defaults to %s.','The root directory that is backed up. Defaults to %s.'=>'The root directory that is backed up. Defaults to %s.','The capability to use when calling %1$s. Defaults to %2$s.'=>'The capability to use when calling %1$s. Defaults to %2$s.','Comma separated list of files or directories to exclude, the backups directory is automatically excluded.'=>'Comma separated list of files or directories to exclude, the backups directory is automatically excluded.','files'=>'files','The path to your %1$s executable. Will be used to zip up your %2$s and %3$s if available.'=>'The path to your %1$s executable. Will be used to zip up your %2$s and %3$s if available.','database'=>'database','The path to your %1$s executable. Will be used for the %2$s part of the back up if available.'=>'The path to your %1$s executable. Will be used for the %2$s part of the back up if available.','e.g.'=>'e.g.','The path to the folder you would like to store your backup files in, defaults to %s.'=>'The path to the folder you would like to store your backup files in, defaults to %s.','You\'ve set it to: %s'=>'You\'ve set it to: %s','The Codex can help'=>'The Codex can help','Constants'=>'Constants','You can %1$s any of the following %2$s in your %3$s to control advanced settings. %4$s. Defined %5$s will be highlighted.'=>'You can %1$s any of the following %2$s in your %3$s to control advanced settings. %4$s. Defined %5$s will be highlighted.','add schedule'=>'add schedule','This is where your backups will appear once you have some.'=>'This is where your backups will appear once you have some.','Actions'=>'Actions','Type'=>'Type','Size'=>'Size','%1$s is returning a %2$s response which could mean cron jobs aren\'t getting fired properly. BackUpWordPress relies on wp-cron to run scheduled backups. See the %3$s for more details.'=>'%1$s is returning a %2$s response which could mean cron jobs aren\'t getting fired properly. BackUpWordPress relies on wp-cron to run scheduled backups. See the %3$s f